`,e(n.p,{children:["However, perhaps the biggest advantage is that a bundler like ",e(n.a,{href:"https://rolldown.rs/",rel:"noreferrer",target:"_blank",children:"Rolldown"})," or ",e(n.a,{href:"https://rspack.dev/",rel:"noreferrer",target:"_blank",children:"Rspack"})," can use the static import statements to remove any code that is not needed. Thus, only the code that is actually used ends up in your production build. This allows us to extend the functionality of the library without increasing your individual bundle size, which is between 1 and 2 kB for most users."]}),`
`,e(n.p,{children:"This can make a big difference, especially for client-side validation and serverless environments, by reducing bundle size and speeding up startup time."}),`
